The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Fraud email fleeces four
                                                                                                               Fraud email fleeces four
          PRONAB MONDAL                                            
	If you receive a message from your email service provider asking for your ID and password, do not respond.         
	At least four Calcuttans have recently been defrauded of thousands of rupees after their friends answered such emails, providing cyber criminals access to their accounts.         
	The four  a prominent doctor, a fashion designer, an official of the Nepal consulate and a research scholar  lodged complaints with the detective departments cyber crime wing in the past month. Those who cheated them could not be caught since they are based abroad, said police.         
	The consulate official said in his complaint: The hacker sent an email from my account to a friend stating that I had been robbed of everything abroad and needed $2,000 immediately. He requested my friend to send the money to the bank account of the hotel where I was supposedly staying. The sender even mentioned that my cellphone was not working abroad.        
	The officials friend immediately sent the money. He did not try to call me once. If he had, he would not have lost the money, said the official.The friends of the other three complainants were defrauded similarly.         
	Cyber criminals are using the names of service providers to obtain the account details of email users. Once they get the details, they hack the accounts, change the password and try various means to siphon off money from the account-holders acquaintances, said Jawed Shamim, the deputy commissioner of the detective department.        
	The police have informed the CBI, the nodal agency of the Interpol, about the crimes. One of the emails originated from the US, said an investigator.                                                                                                                                                                            
